task_description: Facing the building to your North-West (approx. 305°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roofline.
I have seen the top of the building, now I need to look down to see the base to get a full picture of its height.

I have now viewed the building from top to bottom; the ground floor appears to be about 4 meters high, and there are 7 floors above it, each approximately 3 meters high, making the total estimated height 4 + (7 * 3) = 25 meters.
